			<sumFormula>Ag</sumFormula>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Silvering is a chemical process where a non-conducting material is coated with a reflective material, such as glass, to create a mirror. Silver is used as a reflective coating on a second surface to improve bonding between silver and glass. The silver coating on a mirror is very thin, typically only a few atoms thick. The reason mirrors appear silver is because they are made of a well-polished metal surface.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">镀银是一种化学过程，其中非导电材料被涂上反射材料，如玻璃，以创建镜子。银被用作第二表面的反射涂层，以改善银和玻璃之间的粘合。镜子上的银涂层非常薄，通常只有几个原子厚。镜子看起来是银色的原因是因为它们是由精磨的金属表面制成的。</common:generalComment>
